 Notes:

OOPs- Object Oriented Programing Systems.

OOP : It is a design pattern or paradigm , helps to develop real world 
software like ola, uber, flipkart ..etc. by considering real world entities.

OBJECT: object means real world entity which is existing physically. Ex: pen

What is object from java point of view?
	Object is one block of memory which has multiple variable and methods.
	
Why do we need object?
Object is used To represent real world entity in software world.

